      Methods in org.strongback that return DataRecorder 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      static DataRecorder Strongback.dataRecorder()
      Get Strongback's DataRecorder that can be used to register switches, motors, and other functions that provide recordable data.
      DataRecorder DataRecorder.register(String name, DataRecordable recordable)
      Registers by name a recordable object that likely has multiple channels.
      default DataRecorder DataRecorder.register(String name, double scale, DoubleSupplier supplier)
      Registers by name a function that will be periodically polled to obtain a double value and scale it to an integer value that can be recorded.
      DataRecorder DataRecorder.register(String name, IntSupplier supplier)
      Registers by name a function that will be periodically polled to obtain and record an integer value.
      DataRecorder DataRecorder.register(String name, SpeedSensor sensor)
      Registers by name a speed sensor that will be periodically polled to obtain and record the current speed.
      DataRecorder DataRecorder.register(String name, Switch swtch)
      Registers by name a switch that will be periodically polled to obtain and record the switch state.
